FBIS3-17347 "drsov058_s_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-058 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 Georgia Chikvaidze Speaks Following Partnership Signing LD2403174094 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Russian 1611 GMT 24 Mar 94 LD2403174094 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Yesterday Georgia officially joined the Partnership for Peace program, thus becoming the 12th eastern European region country to express their support for the NATO initiative. The document on the partnership was signed by Georgian Foreign Minister Aleksandre Chikvaidze. Speaking at the signing ceremony, he voiced his hope for the deployment of UN troops in Abkhazia, which has declared its independence from Georgia, in order to secure the return of displaced people to their homes from the territory of Abkhazia.
